Embedded System Development Conference China’2005

Embedded System Development Conference China’2005

Guide for Contributors
In this golden Autumn season, the weather is excellent and our Spring City has
surging spring water. Embedded System Development Conference China’ 2005, which
is sponsored by Computer Society Microcomputer (embedded system) subcommittee is
to be held in Jinan, Shandong, a beautiful, historical and cultural city.
The conference is to invite academicians of the two national academies, famous
experts and VIPs from renowned enterprises at home and abroad to deliver keynote
speeches, and at the same time, invites administrative organization of the
profession, research institutes, universities and colleges, high-level personnels
and technical managers from famous embedded system enterprises both at home and
abroad and engineers from applied fields, such as electronics, communication,
information technology to participate in the conference to exchange and to conduct
academic discussions and to explore collectively the technical problems and market
opportunities of all the links of embedded system professional chain. Therefore,
we welcome conference academic papers from experts and scholars both at home and
abroad.

The Theme of the Conference: The latest achievements, development tendency of
embedded technology and embedded system and their applications in all fields. 
Date for the Conference:  Late October 2005
Place for the Conference:  Shandong Jiaotong University in Jinan, Shandong
Contents for the Academic Paper: 
1.	The new structure, technology, developments, products, parts of apparatus,
achievements of SCM and Embedded System;
2.	Emulated platform, development technology, development tools and comprehensive
platform of SCM and Embedded System;
3.	The design of SCM, Embedded System and SOC;
4.	SCM and the operating system, database, software of embedded system;
5.	ASIC, EDA, FPGA, DSP, Multi-MCU and related technology;
6.	The applications of SCM and embedded system:
1)	SCM and embedded system oriented to internet: communication technology,
internet security, broad band switching-on, E-home, etc.
2)	SCM and embedded system oriented to digital consumption electronics:
information home appliances, digital products, entertainment games, etc.
3)	 SCM and embedded system oriented to control: industry control, Security
Protection Monitor & Control, Intelligent Instruments, Medical Equipments, etc.
4)	SCM and embedded system oriented to Automotive Electronics: Car AV System,
Control System, GPS, E-Map, etc.
5)	SCM and embedded system oriented to wireless network: wireless sensor network,
Zigbee, Blue-tooth technology, RFID technology, etc.

After examination, once the academic paper is accepted, the paper is to be
compiled and published at Micro-computer Development.
All the papers are to be written by using WORD file format and send to the
following email address: eschina@jn.gov.cn
Contact Person: Lu Chenxi
Tel: +86-531-86825528   or   +86-13905315250
Website: www.ccfms.org

The deadline for papers is September 30th, 2005 and the date is in accordance with
the distribution date of the paper.

Matters to be noted

All the published papers at official journals at home and abroad and at national
conferences cannot be accepted;
Please do not contribute to another place and the writer is fully responsible for
the paper.
Contributors please mark your detailed contact person, postal address, postcode,
telephone number, fax and email.
Upon receiving the email contributions, the conference sends email reply to the
writer to confirm immediately. If the writer receives no confirmation reply,
please email again or change to postal service.

Paper Format Standard:
1)	The conference requires that the paper should have clear topic, reliable data,
rigor logic and concise language. The length of the paper is to be limited to
within 3000 words (diagrams are included). 
2)	The abstract of the paper should be substantial and detailed. It includes three
parts, namely, research question, process and methods, results and conclusion. The
Chinese abstract is to be limited to 200-250 words, and the English abstract 150
words.
3)	Please mark the derivation of the references used in the paper.

Paper Format Sample:

The Development & Application of Imbedded System and SOC (Center, Mark3-Letter,
black body)

